# Xcelerate Outsourcing — Legacy Workgroup Modernization & Microsoft 365 Transformation

## Project Overview

Xcelerate Outsourcing was operating in a highly fragmented and legacy IT environment with no centralized Active Directory domain, no cloud collaboration platform, and no modern endpoint management. The environment consisted of approximately **40 users** distributed across operational teams, the **Jesmondene Lifestyle Estate division (100+ users)**, and a small **Xcelerate Financial Services unit (2 users)**.

The organization relied heavily on outdated Windows 7 systems, unmanaged workgroup configurations, and insecure shared network drives for business-critical documentation.

The objective of this project was to modernize the entire IT landscape using Microsoft 365 and Azure services, introducing identity governance, secure collaboration, and endpoint standardization.

---

# Existing Environment Assessment

## Identity & Infrastructure

- No Active Directory Domain Controller (DC)
- All systems configured in standalone Workgroup mode
- No centralized authentication system
- Local user accounts across all machines
- Inconsistent password policies

## Endpoint Environment

- Predominantly Windows 7 legacy systems
- Limited hardware standardization
- High security vulnerability exposure (end-of-life OS)
- No endpoint management or monitoring

## File & Collaboration Systems

- Heavy reliance on shared network drives
- Broken and inconsistent folder permissions
- Frequent file duplication and version conflicts
- No backup strategy or retention policy
- No Microsoft Teams or SharePoint usage

---

# Business Units Scope

## Jesmondene Lifestyle Estate (100+ Users)

A large operational division requiring structured document governance and scalable collaboration tooling.

### Key Challenges
- High user volume (~100+ staff)
- Fragmented documentation practices
- No centralized knowledge repository
- Heavy reliance on shared drives

### Solution Delivered
- Dedicated SharePoint Online site collection
- Structured departmental libraries
- Role-based access control
- Standardized document taxonomy

### Outcomes
- Centralized documentation hub
- Improved operational transparency
- Reduced file duplication and data loss

---

## Xcelerate Financial Services (2 Users)

A highly specialized micro-team handling sensitive financial and compliance-related documentation.

### Key Challenges
- Extremely small team (2 users)
- High sensitivity financial data
- Need for strict access control
- No prior collaboration platform

### Solution Delivered
- Isolated SharePoint site with restricted permissions
- Strict RBAC implementation
- Encrypted document storage policies
- Dedicated Teams channel for communication

### Outcomes
- Strong data confidentiality controls
- Secure financial document handling
- Simplified collaboration workflow

