# Project Objectives

## Core Goals

- Introduce Microsoft Entra ID cloud identity platform
- Eliminate reliance on Workgroup-based authentication
- Migrate file shares to SharePoint Online
- Implement Microsoft Teams for collaboration
- Deploy OneDrive for automatic user backup and sync
- Standardize endpoints using Windows 10/11
- Establish secure RBAC and access governance

---

# Phase 1 — Identity & Microsoft 365 Foundation

## Tenant Deployment

- Microsoft 365 tenant created for Xcelerate Outsourcing
- User accounts created for ~40 employees + business units
- Domain configured and verified
- Exchange Online enabled for corporate email

## Entra ID Implementation

- Cloud-based Microsoft Entra ID deployed
- User lifecycle management established
- Password policies enforced
- MFA enabled for all users

---

# Phase 2 — Endpoint Modernization

## Windows Migration Strategy

### Legacy Replacement
- Windows 7 systems identified and decommissioned
- Devices upgraded to Windows 10/11 where hardware permitted
- Non-compliant systems isolated during transition

### Device Standardization
- Baseline security configuration applied
- Defender Antivirus enabled
- BitLocker encryption enforced
- Removal of local admin privileges where possible

---

# Phase 3 — SharePoint Online Migration

## File Share Replacement

### Legacy Problem
- Shared drives with broken permissions
- No version control
- Frequent file overwrites and duplication

### Solution
- Migration to SharePoint Online document libraries
- Department-based site architecture
- Versioning enabled across all libraries
- Sensitivity labels applied to critical data

---

# Phase 4 — Microsoft Teams Deployment

## Collaboration Modernization

- Microsoft Teams rolled out to all users across divisions
- Department-based Teams channels created
- Chat-based communication introduced
- File sharing integrated with SharePoint backend

## Operational Impact

- Reduced dependency on email communication
- Improved cross-team collaboration
- Real-time document co-authoring enabled

---

# Phase 5 — OneDrive for Business Implementation

## User-Level Data Protection

- OneDrive deployed to all users
- Automatic desktop, documents, and pictures backup enabled
- Seamless sync across devices implemented
- Version recovery enabled for user files

## Benefits

- Eliminated local-only file storage risks
- Improved disaster recovery capability
- Enabled secure remote access to user data

---

# Phase 6 — Security Hardening

## Identity Security

- MFA enforced for all accounts
- Legacy authentication blocked
- Risk-based sign-in policies applied

## Endpoint Security

- Microsoft Defender enabled across endpoints
- Device compliance policies enforced
- USB and external storage restrictions applied

## Data Protection

- SharePoint and OneDrive DLP policies implemented
- External sharing restrictions enforced
- Audit logging enabled

---

# Phase 7 — Migration Execution Strategy

## Phased Approach

1. User onboarding into Microsoft 365 tenant
2. Pilot migration group selected
3. Share drive data migration to SharePoint
4. Full OneDrive sync rollout
5. Teams deployment across organization
6. Legacy system decommissioning

---

# Challenges Encountered

## Legacy Windows 7 Environment
Problem:
High number of unsupported systems created security and compatibility issues.

Resolution:
- Phased OS upgrade strategy
- Hardware assessment and replacement planning
- Temporary isolation of high-risk devices

---

## Broken File Share Architecture
Problem:
Severe inconsistency in shared drive permissions and structure.

Resolution:
- Full SharePoint restructuring
- Data cleanup and duplication removal
- Standardized folder taxonomy introduced

